text: Shendzhy () is a rural locality (an aul) and the administrative center of Shendzhyskoye Rural Settlement of Takhtamukaysky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 1942 as of 2018. There are 33 streets. == Ethnicity == The aul is inhabited by Circassians. == References == Category:Rural localities in Takhtamukaysky District
title: Shendzhy
